   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Thirty-three BELIEVE IN THE LORD JESUS Scripture: Acts 16:30-31 Who is the Lord Jesus?</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>He is the Lord who created the universe.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>He is also the God who is our Savior.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>He is Jesus who is God become a man.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>He is the One who is God and also is a man.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>He became man to bear our sins.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>And because He is God, He is also able to forgive our sins.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>What did the Lord Jesus do?</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>He died and shed His blood on the cross for our sins.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>He resurrected from the dead in order that we might have life.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Because of His death and resurrection He became the Savior of our whole being.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>What should we do with the Lord Jesus?</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Acknowledge that He is the Savior of all mankind.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Acknowledge that He is our Savior, that He died and resurrected for us.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Receive Him as our Savior.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The unit of the Lord s salvation</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Even though the salvation of the Lord comes to an individual, God s intention is that the entire household unit receive salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The salvation of the Lord comes not only to an individual, but also to the whole household.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Therefore the Word says, Believe on the Lord Jesus, and thou shalt be saved, thou and thy house.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The result of salvation Sins are forgiven.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Eternal life is obtained.</S>
   </TEXT>
